This file describes the hirarchy of Simulation Techiniques.  Its
purpose is to clarify the \emph{theoretical} inheritance properties of the
various simulation tools.

\section{Simulation Techinques}

        Explore the properties of a statisitcal distribution by
        creating samples from the distribution and evaluating the properties
        of the sample.

\subsection{Resampleing Methods}
        
        Generate samples by using the observed data

        Required function:
        \begin{itemize}
        \item generate sample given observed data
        \end{itemize}
          


\subsection{Pure Monte-Carlo}

        Generate the samples directly from the distribution of interest

        Required function:
        \begin{itemize}
        \item generate sample given distribution of interest
        \end{itemize}

\subsection{Markov Chain Monte-Carlo}

        Generate samples by simulating from a process that converges to the distribution of interest.

        Required function: 
        \begin{itemize}
        \item  generate next state in process given current state
        \end{itemize}


\subsubsection{General Metropolis-Hastings Update Method}

        Generate the next sample by making a "guess" and then evaluating whether to use the guess or stay at the current state.

        Required functions: 
        \begin{itemize}
        \item proposal function -- generate guess given current state 
        \item acceptance function -- decide whether to use guess or keep current state (usually dependes on target distribution)
        \end{itemize}


\begin{enumerate}

\item Metropolis-Hastings 

        Generate the next sample by making a "guess".  Evaluate whether to use or keep using the Metropolis-Hastings acceptance function

        Required Functions: 
        \begin{itemize}
        \item proposal function
        \item target distribution
        \end{itemize}


\begin{enumerate}

\item Metropolis 

        Generate the next sample symmetrically.  IE,  
        \[ P(y \to x) = P(x \to y) \mbox{ for all } x, y. \]

        Reqired Functions 
        \begin{itemize}
        \item symmetric proposal function
        \item target distribution
        \end{itemize}


\begin{enumerate}

\item Gibbs Sampler

        Generate the next sample from the full conditional distribution of each variable, conditional on all others
        IE,  
        \[ P(x_{t+1,i}=y) = P( X_i=y | X_{i+1} = x_{t,i+1} , \dots , X_p = x_{t,p},  X_{t+1} = x_{t+1,1} , .. , X_{i-1} = x_{t+1,i-1} ) \]
        
        Required Functions:
        \begin{itemize}
        \item full conditional proposal function
        \end{itemize}
            

\end{enumerate}

\end{enumerate}

\end{enumerate}

